article.headline: VMI 120, Virginia-Wise 88
article.story: LEXINGTON, Va. -- Stan Okoye had a career-high 28 points with 10 rebounds to lead Virginia Military Institute to a 120-88 win over Virginia-Wise on Tuesday night and the Keydets' first 3-0 start since the 1985-86 season. Keith Gabriel scored 27 points and freshman Rodney Glasgow chipped in a career-high 23 points, with five steals and four assists. VMI shot 34 of 38 from the free-throw line, including 19 of 20 in the second half. The Keydets also forced 25 turnovers, including 13 in the second half when the NAIA Cavaliers (4-2) shot 37.8 percent from the field (14 of 37). However, VMI trailed by as many as six points in the first half until an Okoye basket at the 10:17 mark tied the score at 29. The Keydets went on to a 68-48 halftime advantage as Okoye scored 19 first-half points. Sam Eligwe led Virginia-Wise with 18 points and Norris Gaskins added 15.
